b and His D.J. Gig</a>.=E2=80=9D Apparently it is possible to have conflict=
s of interest between running Goldman Sachs and DJing, and Solomon might ha=
ve found some, and others at Goldman have griped about them.=C2=A0</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">And today=E2=80=99s Wall Street Journal has a =
story with the headline =E2=80=9C<a href=3D"https://link.mail.bloombergbusi=
ness.com/click/31780057.258413/aHR0cHM6Ly93d3cud3NqLmNvbS9hcnRpY2xlcy9nb2xk=
bWFuLXNhY2hzLWNlby1kYXZpZC1zb2xvbW9uLWRqLWJvbnVzZXMtMWE0N2RiZjU_bW9kPWhwX2x=
lYWRfcG9zNQ/607f07ceef4b8524a319a23cB19400256" itemprop=3D"StoryLink" items=
cope=3D"itemscope" target=3D"_blank" style=3D"color: #000000; text-decorati=
on: none !important; border-bottom-width: 1px; border-bottom-color: #000000=
; border-bottom-style: solid; background-color: #ccc;">Goldman Sachs Is at =
War With Itself</a>=E2=80=9D that begins with this story:</p>
<blockquote>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">When Goldman Sachs partners descended on Miami=
 Beach for the bank=E2=80=99s annual confab of senior leaders in February, =
it was a former CEO, Lloyd Blankfein, who stole the show.</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">Blankfein, holding court at the hotel bar befo=
re a gathering of Goldman partners, groused about his successor, according =
to people familiar with the matter. David Solomon, Blankfein said, was spen=
ding too much time away from his day job, jetting around on Goldman=E2=80=
=99s private planes and DJing at nightclubs and festivals.=C2=A0</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">Blankfein wasn=E2=80=99t the only one complain=
ing. Partners faulted Solomon, who wasn=E2=80=99t present at the bar, for p=
residing over a money-losing expansion into consumer lending that Goldman i=
s now unwinding. The consumer business, they said, didn=E2=80=99t make the =
partners money. That stood in contrast with the bank=E2=80=99s other units.=
</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">Cracks are forming in a Wall Street institutio=
n: the vaunted Goldman Sachs partnership.=C2=A0</p>
</blockquote>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">And one of the conservative older bankers who =
advised against the DJing=C2=A0is actually named:</p>
<blockquote><p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">John Rogers, a Goldman partner sin=
ce 2000, and the secretary to the bank=E2=80=99s board, expressed concerns =
to Solomon about his DJ side gig, according to people familiar with the mat=
ter, saying it wasn=E2=80=99t a good look for the CEO of one of Wall Street=
=E2=80=99s most formidable firms.</p></blockquote>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">Just an absolutely Shakespearean palace coup b=
rewing here, all these Goldman partners plotting revolt because their CEO i=
s also a DJ.=C2=A0</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">I am =E2=80=A6=C2=A0partially =E2=80=A6=C2=A0k=
idding? Actually the disputes seem to be more about money and strategy and,=
 in particular, the power of the Goldman partnership:</p>
<blockquote>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">Since the late 1800s, Goldman partners have we=
ighed in on the firm=E2=80=99s direction. They conveyed their opinions to G=
oldman=E2=80=99s chief=E2=80=94for a long time known as the senior partner=
=E2=80=94and engaged in debate. Partners sometimes overruled the CEO or per=
suaded him to go along with their plans.=C2=A0</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">For a long time, the CEO was viewed as one of =
many, less a benign dictator and more the bank=E2=80=99s public face and st=
andard-bearer. Blankfein often behaved like the senior partner, people fami=
liar with the matter said, preferring persuasion to decree when it came to =
decision-making.</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">Things changed when Solomon got the top job in=
 2018. ...=C2=A0</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">Solomon, the first CEO who didn=E2=80=99t work=
 at the bank when it was a private partnership, did away with the flat hier=
archy that gave partners wide leeway to call their own shots. Longtime part=
ners said they found it harder to communicate with Solomon than Blankfein, =
who encouraged people to stop by his office for informal chats.</p>
</blockquote>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">Solomon=E2=80=99s model is that Goldman Sachs =
is a publicly traded corporation and he is the chief executive officer of i=
t. That model is factually accurate, but Goldman has spent a long time sort=
 of pretending that it is in fact a private partnership, largely for good c=
ultural and risk-management reasons, and you can see why the partners would=
 be attached to=C2=A0<em>that=C2=A0</em>model.</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">Meanwhile at Semafor, <a href=3D"https://link.=
mail.bloombergbusiness.com/click/31780057.258413/aHR0cHM6Ly93d3cuc2VtYWZvci=
5jb20vYXJ0aWNsZS8wNi8xMi8yMDIzL3ByaXZhdGUtZXF1aXR5LWJpZGRlcnMtY2lyY2xlLXRoZ=
S1yZW1haW5zLW9mLWdvbGRtYW5zLW1haW4tc3RyZWV0LWFtYml0aW9ucw/607f07ceef4b8524a=
319a23cB6d9638a2" itemprop=3D"StoryLink" itemscope=3D"itemscope" target=3D"=
_blank" style=3D"color: #000000; text-decoration: none !important; border-b=
ottom-width: 1px; border-bottom-color: #000000; border-bottom-style: solid;=
 background-color: #ccc;">Liz Hoffman reports</a>:</p>
<blockquote>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">Less than two years after Goldman Sachs paid n=
early $2 billion for a specialty lender, the firm is now unwinding the deal=
 at a significant loss as it retreats from its ambitions on Main Street.</p=
>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">Apollo, Sixth Street, and Warburg Pincus are a=
mong the investment firms that submitted initial bids on Friday valuing the=
 business, once known as GreenSky, at mid-nine figures, people familiar wit=
h the matter said.</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">Goldman put GreenSky up for sale in April, whe=
n CEO David Solomon said it no longer fit with the bank=E2=80=99s =E2=80=9C=
current strategic priorities.=E2=80=9D His lieutenant, John Waldron, said a=
t an investment conference earlier this month that a sale could result in a=
 $500 million writedown.</p>
</blockquote>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">Took their eyes off the ball because of all th=
e DJing, etc.</p>
