e7c9df42" itemprop=3D"StoryLink" itemscope=3D"itemscope" target=3D"_blank" =
style=3D"color: #000000; text-decoration: none !important; border-bottom-wi=
dth: 1px; border-bottom-color: #000000; border-bottom-style: solid; backgro=
und-color: #ccc;">  this made me chuckle</a>:</p>
<blockquote>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">Just over two years ago, Deutsche Bank AG=E2=
=80=99s investment arm eliminated the managing director title.=C2=A0</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">Frustration over the policy that dispensed wit=
h some corporate designations at Frankfurt-based DWS Group means management=
 is now considering bringing them back, according to people familiar with t=
he matter.=C2=A0</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">Chief Executive Officer Stefan Hoops is weighi=
ng whether once to again to allow staff to use titles like =E2=80=98managin=
g director=E2=80=99 and =E2=80=98director=E2=80=99 to describe their rank, =
for example on business cards, the people said, asking not to be named disc=
ussing the private matter. =E2=80=A6</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">Among criticism expressed with the policy at D=
WS was a feeling that it had slowed career progression and sowed confusion =
about seniority, the people said. =E2=80=A6</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">Instead of corporate titles, DWS now uses func=
tional titles such as =E2=80=9Chead of=E2=80=9D to describe someone=E2=80=
=99s actual responsibilities, rather than their position on the corporate l=
adder.</p>
</blockquote>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">Yeah I can see how that would be confusing. Ev=
eryone is the head of something, and how do you know how important the thin=
g you are head of is if you don=E2=80=99t have a title?=C2=A0</p>
